		  Ubuntu 7 on IBM Lenovo ThinkPad T60p
			     Install Notes

		       David Lyons lyons@lvc.edu

6/2/2007

Had trouble with fedora 7, installed but then hung on first boot.
Decided to try ubuntu, which we had tried on live cd.

Booted live cd, installed from there.

Used built-in Add/Remove and 
% sudo apt-get install packagename
to install a bunch of things, here are some
  emacs
  tetex
    7/24 discovered beamer package and related packages were missing,
    could not process talk slides I made with beamer in the spring.  I
    downloaded beamer, pgf and xcolor from sourceforge, I got the link
    to them from the beamer home page, installed it.  Run 
      % sudo texhash
    after putting the files in the tex directory tree.
  xfig
  gnuplot
  fvwm
  java

Things work well, interface is nice, speed is good.  Wireless at home
and at open connections is easy using network manager tool on toolbar.
So far cannot get wireless to work on LVC network.  Will continue to
try.

New firefox works fine with google spreadsheets, resolving old speed and
system bog down problem with fedora core 5.  Fedora 7 and its firefox
also work.

migrated personal directory stuff
  .emacs
  .fvwm2rc
  .gnupg
  .bashrc
  ~/a and subdirectories
  mkdir downloads
  mkdir tmp
  ~/.scripts
  ~/.gaim

