6/5/2007 

wireless at LVC, success!

  1. install wpasupplicant
     sudo apt-get install wpasupplicant

  2. edit /etc/wpa_supplicant.conf

network={
	ssid="wpublic"
	scan_ssid=1
	key_mgmt=IEEE8021X
	eap=PEAP
	identity="usernamehere"
	password="passwdhere"
}

  3. do this to connect, yee ha!
     sudo wpa_supplicant -iath0 -c/etc/wpa_supplicant.conf -Dmadwifi -w
     sudo dhclient ath0

  4. don't click on network manager icon, it'll mess you up!

Comment: even though the connection is working, it cuts in and out a lot.  This
  is the way it has always been, I think.

  another useful command, a command line to scan for networks
    sudo iwlist scanning

6/6/2007

  5. automate startup

wrote script ~/.scripts/lvcwirelessstart

#!/bin/sh

# 6/6/2007 works!
#  can we set up a clickable launcher?

sudo -b wpa_supplicant -iath0 -c/etc/wpa_supplicant.conf -Dmadwifi -w
sudo -b dhclient ath0

		     =============================
		     end of wireless configuration
		     =============================

control startup programs on login

    * System -> Preferences -> Sessions
        Startup Programs Tab -> Add/Edit/Delete

    I unchecked firefox.  It was listed under "No Name".  Sinister?

disable the touchpad

  a. edit /etc/X11/xorg.conf, find the section for synaptics, add the
  line that turns on option SHMConfig

Section "InputDevice"
	Identifier	"Synaptics Touchpad"
	Driver	         "synaptics"
        Option          "SHMConfig"             "on"
	Option		"SendCoreEvents"	"true"
	Option		"Device"		"/dev/psaux"
	Option		"Protocol"		"auto-dev"
	Option		"HorizScrollDelta"	"0"
EndSection

restart the X server, then

  b. execute this command
$ synclient TouchpadOff=1

  b'. automated version, System > Preferences > Sessions > (Startup
  Programs tab) New
synclient TouchpadOff=1

java under firefox
    somehowe installed java, then
    sudo ln -s /usr/lib/jre1.6.0_01/plugin/i386/ns7/libjavaplugin_oji.so /usr/lib/mozilla-firefox/plugins/libjavaplugin_oji.so  
    go figure

fix emacs M-x print-buffer
  found a decent fix, use Postscript print buffer 
  M-x ps-print-buffer

General comments: some configuring has been a pain, but overall,
installs are easy and there's documentation out there.  I like the
distro so far after a week of fussing and experimenting.

installed google toolbar, this let me choose to have gmail be my default
mail client, so when you click on a mailto link, you go straight to a
compose message window in gmail.  There's a lot more there that I'll
have to experiment with.

6/8/2007

just discovered a problem with dvips for tex files.  Somehow the file
just does not go to the printer.  A workaround is

% dvips -t letter -o filename.ps filename.dvi
% lpr filename.ps

but I need to figure out how to configure dvips properly.

another problem: function buttons (F1 F2 etc) for which I have defined
keyboard shortcuts for emacs have been taken over by the terminal.  Need
to unset the terminal behavior and give the control back to emacs.



